message.content: One of the most significant events that took place in Slovenia in the past 5 years was the Slovenian parliamentary election held on June 3, 2018. It marked a significant political shift as the anti-establishment party, known as the Slovenian Democratic Party (SDS), led by Janez Janša, emerged as the largest party in the National Assembly. The election resulted in a change of government, with Janez Janša becoming the Prime Minister of Slovenia for the third time. This event had a notable impact on Slovenian politics and policies, as it brought a new direction and leadership to the country.
